      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/neovim-multiple-configs/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 class=&#34;heading&#34; id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Intro&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#intro&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you&amp;rsquo;re Neovim fan, it is important to have multiple configs. You can configure like this:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;~/.config/nvim&lt;/code&gt;: Your main configuration. When you&amp;rsquo;re working on your project, this is the configuration that will be loaded.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;~/.config/nvim-alt&lt;/code&gt;: Your secondary Neovim configuration where you can implement new things.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;So now, let&amp;rsquo;s configure it.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;heading&#34; id=&#34;setup-neovim-playground&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Setup Neovim Playground&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#setup-neovim-playground&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Assuming that your main Neovim configured, let&amp;rsquo;s configure the alternate Neovim configuration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
